stylometry: Elasticity of demand is the sensitivity of price when it comes to demand.  Price and demand are directly related, if demand goes up or down, so does price.  They are dependent on each other. It is important to know the elasticity when dealing with business like decisions because it can alter and change the reasons why a decision would be made. If the price of a complementary item goes up, so would the other item. In terms of a peanut butter and jelly sandwich, if the price and demand of jelly goes up, the price and demand of peanut butter would also go up.
